CatDescriptText: This photograph may have been taken as part of an application for a Liquor Control Board license for Vince's Bar.  A stuffed deer head and two landscape paintings hang above the bar.  The room is trimmed with neon, with "Vince's" written in neon above the center of the bar.  Images of boxers decorate the mirrors.  The room has a pressed tin ceiling, tile floor, and large wooden bar with chrome stools.  Booths line the wall to the right, with a men's room and a pinball machine in the background.  On the far right, in front of the men's room, a man's arm and shoulder can be seen.
TitMainTitle: Interior of Vinces' Bar, with diamond patterned mosaic tile floor, landscape paintings, mounted deer head, and pinball machine
